<F P=100> INTER-ASIA AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Meeting on East Timor Held in Manila </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Meeting on East Timor Held in Manila </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Visas of 10 Foreigners Cancelled </H4>

<F P=102> BK0106124594 Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network in Tagalog 
0500 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0106124594 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Tagalog </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Bureau of Immigration and Deportation [BID] 
today cancelled the visas of 10 foreign nationals currently 
attending the Asia-Pacific Conference on East Timor [APCET]. 
Immigration Associate Commissioner Manuel Roxas reiterated that 
their action is in compliance with the government's position to 
bar foreigners attending the conference. Those foreigners who 
are now attending the APCET are believed to have gained entry 
into the country before their ban took effect. 
  In this connection, immigration agents headed by Tom 
Natividad this morning served summons on 10 foreigners attending 
the conference at the Malcolm Hall of the University of the 
Philippines. Natividad said the foreigners should personally go 
to the immigration office before 0800. He clarified that they 
went to Malcolm Hall just to serve the subpoenas to the 
foreigners and not to arrest them. 
  [Begin recording, in English] [Natividad] As I have said, we 
are just instructed to serve these to the secretariat, and 
that's all. 
  [Unidentified correspondent] Sir, if they do not appear, 
what 
will happen? 
  [Natividad] I don't know. 
  [Unidentified correspondent] Sir, what's your name again? 
  [Natividad] Tom Natividad. Intelligence Officer Tom 
Natividad. 
  [Indistinct question from unidentified correspondent] 
  [Natividad] No, it's not. (?It's) a subpoena that they have 
to appear at 0800 today. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

