  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, June 1 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The Asian 
Bank for Development is granting to Mongolia some 25 million US 
dollars worth of credits for the purpose of promoting the 
development of telecommunications system in the country. The 
talks on this matter were held recently in Manila where 
participating was Vice President of the Mongolbank S. 
Chuluunbat. According to him, in granting of those credits 
other foreign countries are to take part too. For instance, the 
Government of Norway decided to provide together with some other 
Scandinavian countries 18 million USD credits part of which 
would be granted in the form of gratis aid. 

