<H4>    Kakizawa Comments on U.S.-DPRK Talks </H4>

<F P=102> OW0106121894 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 1 Jun 94 
Morning Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0106121894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] During a 31 May session of the House of 
Representatives Budget Committee, Yoshimi Mino of the opposition 
Social Democratic Party of Japan indicated, "North Korea has a 
feeling that the UN Security Council and the International 
Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) are under the control of the United 
States," and he then asked, "Does the DPRK not aim to negotiate 
with the United States for a normalization of relations between 
the two countries?" Foreign Minister Koji Kakizawa replied, 
"The DPRK appears to be intending to settle the issue of the 
replacement of fuel rods at the experimental nuclear reactor in 
North Korea through talks with the United States." The foreign 
minister also stated, "I consider what Mr. Mino just indicated 
to be our view." 

</TEXT>

