<H4>    PRC Asked To Persuade DPRK </H4>

<F P=102> OW0106115294 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 31 May 
Evening Edition p 1 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0106115294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Speaking at a news conference on the morning of 31 
May at the end of a cabinet session, Foreign Minister Koji 
Kakizawa touched on the issue of North Korea's suspected 
development of nuclear weapons and said, "I have heard that the 
Japanese Embassy in Beijing is already in contact with the 
Chinese Government." In this way the foreign minister disclosed 
that the Japanese Government is asking the Chinese Government 
through the Japanese Embassy in Beijing to persuade North Korea. 
At the news conference, the foreign minister also disclosed 
that Japan and South Korea have continued to discuss the issue 
with the United States through their embassies and missions in 
New York and Washington, adding, "Although I cannot disclose all 
the Japanese Government is doing, the Japanese Government is 
doing everything it can in an effort to resolve the issue." 

</TEXT>

