<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Reaction to DPRK Nuclear Issue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Reaction to DPRK Nuclear Issue </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    DPRK Moves To Test-Fire Missile </H4>

<F P=102> OW3105131294 Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN in Japanese 31 May 94 
Morning Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW3105131294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Commenting on North Korea's moves to test-fire a 
missile at a news conference on 30 May, Chief Cabinet Secretary 
Hiroshi Kumagai said, "The government has information on those 
moves in that country." In this way, the Japanese Government 
officially confirmed for the first time North Korea's moves to 
test-fire the missile. 
  At the news conference, however, Chief Cabinet Secretary 
Kumagai stated: "The government does not know details of North 
Korea's plans to test-fire the missile. The government also does 
not know whether North Korea's moves to test-fire the missile 
are related to the issue of international inspections of its 
nuclear facilities. I, therefore, would like to refrain from 
making any further comment at the present stage." 

</TEXT>

