<H3> <TI>   Sakigake's Takemura on SDPJ Return to Coalition </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sakigake's Takemura on SDPJ Return to Coalition </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW3105122594 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 30 May 
94 Morning Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW3105122594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Masayoshi Takemura, head of Sakigake [Harbinger], 
held a news conference in Matsue City on 29 May, in which he 
commented on the possibility of the cabinet resigning en masse 
to pave the way for the Social Democratic Party of Japan's 
[SDPJ] return to the coalition government. He said that his 
response to SDPJ Secretary General Wataru Kubo's remark seeking 
the voluntary resignation of the cabinet was, "The SDPJ's return 
to the coalition by resigning en masse is improbable." This is 
an attempt to restrain ongoing moves in the SDPJ. 

</TEXT>

