<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   JNP Defectors' Strategy Include Governor Yokomichi </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    JNP Defectors' Strategy Include Governor Yokomichi </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0206085494 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 30 May 94 
Evening Edition p 1 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0206085494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] It was disclosed on 30 May that an interparty 
policy group of liberals will be formed in June at the 
initiative of the Minshu no Kaze [Democratic Wind], a group of 
four defectors from the Japan New Party [JNP]. Members of the 
Minshu no Kaze intend to gather about 60 Dietmen from such 
parties as the Social Democratic Party of Japan [SDPJ], the 
Sakigake [Harbinger], and the Group Seiun. Hokkaido Governor 
Takahiro Yokomichi, who recently announced his decision not to 
pursue his third reappointment as the governor, is also invited 
to the group to encourage his return to the Diet. The group 
probably intends to receive Yokomichi as a leader of liberals. 
  The policy group is expected to be called the "Council on 
Concept of Democrat Government" (tentative name), and the first 
preparatory meeting will be held on 1 June. Members of the 
Minshu no Kaze and SDPJ Deputy Secretary General Masanori Goto 
have informally asked Governor Yokomichi to join the group. 
Some of them want to receive Yokomichi as the leader of the 
group when he comes back to the Diet. Asked about this at the 
Hokkaido Prefectural Government on the morning of 30 May, 
Governor Yokomichi avoided making clear comments on his own 
position in the group, saying: "They are not asking me to 
become the leader (of the policy group). Since the group is 
designed as a gathering of Diet members, I am not going to do 
something special in the group." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

