<F P=101> Burma </F>
<H3> <TI>   Construction Minister Returns From PRC </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Construction Minister Returns From PRC </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK3005071394 Rangoon Radio Burma in Burmese 1330 GMT 29 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3005071394 </F>
<F P=104>  Rangoon Radio Burma </F>
<F P=105>  Burmese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A five-member Myanmar [Burmese] delegation led by 
Construction Minister U Khin Maung Yin, which paid a goodwill 
visit to the People's Republic of China [PRC] at the invitation 
of PRC's minister of railways, this afternoon returned to Yangon 
[Rangoon] by Myanmar airways International flight via Singapore. 
  The minister was welcomed at Yangon airport by Brigadier 
General Maung Maung, minister of livestock breeding and 
fisheries; Colonel Pe Thein, minister of prime minister's 
office; Col. Aung San, deputy minister of construction; Mr. 
Liang Feng, ambassador of the PRC; responsible personnel, 
friends, and family members. 

</TEXT>

