<H3> <TI>   Laos Agrees To Help Curb Log Smuggling </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Laos Agrees To Help Curb Log Smuggling </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2905144994 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 0500 GMT 29 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2905144994 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 0500 GMT 29 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] [Passage omitted] Lao Deputy Foreign Minister 
Souban Srithirat told foreign journalists his ministry has 
received an official letter from the Royal Government of 
Cambodia [RGC] in April asking Laos to cooperate by closing its 
border passes to block the smuggling of Cambodian logs into or 
through Laos into Thailand. 
  Souban Srithirat added that the Lao Government has already 
responded to the RGC's request and that Laos would implement the 
policy of blocking log smuggling from Cambodia through Laos in 
all areas bordering Laos and Cambodia, particularly in the Stung 
Treng-Champassak, Ratanakiri-Attopeu, and areas in Preah Vihear 
Province bordering Laos. [Passage omitted]. 

</TEXT>

