<H3> <TI>   NADK Denies Involvement With Missing Foreigners </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NADK Denies Involvement With Missing Foreigners </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2805104594 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2805104594 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>

<F P=105>  Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Statement" of the National Army of Democratic Kampuchea </F>
rejecting slanderous remarks against Democratic Kampuchea 
concerning missing foreigners -- read by announcer] 
  [Text] I. The allies, communist Vietnamese, and communist 
Vietnamese puppets recently made remarks slandering Democratic 
Kampuchea concerning the case of missing foreigners. 
  II. The National Army of Democratic Kampuchea [NADK] 
spokesman vehemently rejects these slanderous remarks and wishes 
to clarify the matter as follows: 
  A. We are not involved in this matter. There is no reason 
for us to commit such an abominable act like the allies, 
communist Vietnamese, and communist Vietnamese puppets who 
always claim to be democratic or masters of human rights despite 
the fact that they have killed hundreds of thousands and even 
millions of people. 
  B. We have strived and are striving to end the war and to 
bring about genuine national reconciliation and peace so that 
the people can lead a normal life and earn their living 
peacefully. 
  [Dated] 27 May 1994 
  [Signed] The NADK spokesman 

</TEXT>

