<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   Delegation Departs for Nonaligned Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Delegation Departs for Nonaligned Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2805100994 Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network in 
Lao 0000 GMT 28 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2805100994 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Lao </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This morning, a Lao delegation headed by Souban 
Salitthilat, deputy foreign affairs minister, left Vientiane for 
Cairo, Egypt, to attend the 17th nonaligned ministerial 
conference from 30 May to 3 June. 
  Over the past more than 30 years, the Nonaligned Movement 
has 
firmly adhered to its principle aimed at safeguarding world 
peace, contributing to the struggle for national liberation and 
disarmament, and speaking against racial discrimination and for 
improved living conditions of people in developing countries, 
thus making it an influential political force in the 
international arena. 
  At the Cairo ministerial conference, the Movement will 
discuss various issues, including its future and program of 
action, particularly in contributing towards making the United 
Nations more democratic so it will heed the interests of all 
countries -- be they big or small, developed or underdeveloped. 
In addition, the Movement will also discuss the forthcoming 
eleventh summit, cooperation between the Nonaligned Movement and 
other international organizations, economic cooperation, human 
rights issues, the environment, and so forth. 

</TEXT>

