<F P=100> Philippines </F>
<H3> <TI>   GNP Grows in First Quarter of 1994 </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    GNP Grows in First Quarter of 1994 </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0206062094 Quezon City Radio Filipinas in English 0230 GMT 
2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0206062094 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City Radio Filipinas </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The country's gross national product [GNP] grew by 
4.84 percent in the first quarter of the year. That's a big 
leap compared to last year's 0.27 percent to the same period. 
Economic Planning Secretary Cielito Habito calls it a 
remarkable (?sailing). The growth rate was the highest recorded 
in the past three years. Habito said it meant new jobs for 
Filipinos and open business opportunities for local industries. 
Habito said at least 200,000 jobs would have been available 
starting last month. Habito also said prospects for the rest of 
the year are even brighter despite fears of rising prices of 
petroleum products and basic goods as a result of the 
implementation of expanded value-added tax. 

</TEXT>

