<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   King Appoints Banhan Sinlapa-acha Opposition Head </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    King Appoints Banhan Sinlapa-acha Opposition Head </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0106133394 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in Thai 1200 GMT 
1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0106133394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>
<F P=105>  Thai </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Announcement" signed by King Phumiphon Adunyadet and </F>
countersigned by House of Representatives President Marut 
Bunnak; issued on 27 May, place not given] 
  [Text] His royal signature: Phumiphon Adunyadet 
  Whereas a royal decree was issued on 30 October 1992 
appointing Police General Praman Adireksan as opposition leader 
in the House of Representatives, Police Gen. Praman has resigned 
as leader of the Chat Thai Party, thus disqualifying him as 
opposition leader in the House of Representatives. Therefore, 
he loses his position as per Article 116, Paragraph 3 of the 
1991 Constitution. 
  The king deems that Banhan Sinlapa-acha possesses the 
qualifications required by Article 116, Paragraph 3 of the 1991 
Constitution and is suitable to be leader of the opposition in 
the House of Representatives. Therefore, he appoints Banhan 
Sinlapa-acha as opposition leader in the House of 
Representatives from this moment onward. 
  Announced on 27 May 1994, the 49th year of the reign of the 
present king. 
  Countersigned by House of Representatives President Marut 
Bunnak. 

</TEXT>

