<H3> <TI>   Ship With Chinese Docks at Christmas Island </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ship With Chinese Docks at Christmas Island </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2905144794 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 1100 GMT 
29 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2905144794 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A vessel carrying 58 people believed to be from 
China has docked at Christmas Island in the Indian Ocean, north 
of Western Australia. The 11 women and 47 men were met by 
Australian federal police, and immigration and customs officials 
when they landed. The radio messages had been intercepted by 
Christmas Island officials. 
  Federal police spokesman, (Richard Crobbers), says it is 
believed that fishing vessel had left China about one month ago. 
He says they will be moved to mainland Australia within the 
next few days. 

</TEXT>

