<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Phan Van Khai Receives German Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Phan Van Khai Receives German Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2805095194 Hanoi VNA in English 0619 GMT 28 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2805095194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA May 28 -- Vice Premier Phan Van Khai 
received in Hanoi yesterday German Minister of Cooperation and 
Development Carl-Dieter Spranger and his party now on a working 
visit to Vietnam. 
  Speaking to his guests, Vice Premier Phan Van Khai 
reiterated 
the fine development of Vietnam-Germany relations in recent 
years. On behalf of the prime minister, Vice Premier Khai 
expressed his thanks to the German Government and people for 
their assistance and cooperation with Vietnam in socio-economic 
development, especially in afforestation, environment 
protection, poverty alleviation and hunger eradication and in 
generation for workers returned from Germany. 
  The vice premier highly valued the possibility in capital 
and 
technology of Germany and noted that the Vietnam-Germany 
relations of cooperation and friendship in the interest of the 
two countries should be further promoted in accordance with the 
potential of Vietnam and Germany. He also said that Vietnam 
will create favourable conditions for German businessmen to 
invest into Vietnam. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

