  Meanwhile, 105-mm artillery groups and bandits of the puppet 
army took combat positions in Paju and Yonchon Counties, Kyonggi 
Province, and Chorwon County, South Korean Kangwon Province, and 
fired more than 300 shells and bullets of large-caliber 
machineguns at spots adjacent to the Demilitarized Zone along 
the Military Demarcation Line. 

