<H3> <TI>   U.S. Congresswoman Urges Improved DPRK Ties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Congresswoman Urges Improved DPRK Ties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2805060594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0551 GMT 28 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2805060594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 28 (KCNA) -- U.S. Congresswoman 
Elizabeth Purse demanded a switchover in the Korea policy of the 
U.S. 
  In her letter of April 8 to the U.S. President and to the 
chairman of the House Armed Services Committee, she expressed 
concern over U.S. armed threat to North Korea. 
  No one says North Korea is producing nuclear fissionable 
materials, but the United States alone insists on that 
possibility, she said. 
  War preparations against North Korea do not conform to the 
supreme interests of the United States, she said, adding that 
she thinks the United States must not escalate tensions but 
pursue a policy for normalising relations with North Korea. 
  "Under the current situation," she said, "we must continue 
to 
use diplomatic means and improve relations with North Korea." 

</TEXT>

