<H3> <TI>   ROK Groups Invited To Discuss National Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ROK Groups Invited To Discuss National Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0206051594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0440 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0206051594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- Chairwoman of the C.C. 
[Central Committee], the Chondoist Chongu Party Yu Mi-yong in a 
statement Wednesday urged the political parties and religious 
organizations of South Korea to accede to a contact at an 
earlier date to discuss the convocation of a national conference. 
  She said the choice of the entire fellow countrymen for 
warding off the danger of a nuclear war hanging over the nation, 
defending peace of the country and opening a signal phase for 
the independent and peaceful reunification of the country is the 
great unity of the whole nation and the convocation of a 
national conference that may help pool the patriotic will and 
efforts of the nation. 
  "We Chondoist believers cannot give up our hope for a 
national conference although a tiny handful of those in South 
Korea opposed to dialogue and reunification are laying hurdles 
in our way," she said, and added: "We urge that our Chondoist 
Chongu Party and political parties of South Korea should have 
bilateral or multilateral contacts at an early date to discuss 
the convocation of a national conference." 
  She expressed the hope that the South Korean authorities, 
though belatedly, would show a positive response to the proposal 
for ont vocation of a national conference and take due measures 
to select promptly South side's delegates to the preparatory 
committee for a national conference so that the committee might 
tackle down to its task. 

</TEXT>

