<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 28 (KCNA) -- Rallies of workers were 
held at factories in Pyongyang supporting and encouraging the 
struggle of the South Korean workers for wage hike. 
  The speakers at the rallies said that the South Korean 
workers were paid less than one fourth of the minimum living 
cost for their intensive labour of longest working hour in the 
world. But the Kim Yong-sam group is pursuing even the 
wage-curbing policy under the pretext of "share of pains", they 
noted. 
  Charging that the South Korean puppet clique issued an order 
to brand the struggle of the workers for wage hike and 
"labour-management dispute" as illegal to severely counter 
them and mobilised all the repressive forces to crack down on 
them at the point of bayonet, they said: 
  "If the South Korean workers vacillate in the present-day 
struggle or pin any illusion and expectation on the authorities 
and enterpreneurs, it will result in binding them faster to the 
chains of oppression and capital," the speakers said, and 
stressed: 
  The South Korean workers must give a teaching to the 
exploiters in concerted efforts. 
  The South Korean workers must wage a vigorous struggle to 
get 
U.S. imperialist forces of aggression withdrawn from South 
Korea, abolish the fascist laws and repressive tools, let the 
present "civilian" government resign and establish a genuine 
independent government. 
  The working class in the northern palf of Korea will achieve 
the reunification of the country without fail by pooling efforts 
with the South Korean workers. 

</TEXT>

