<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Koreans in Japan Protest Crackdown on Chongnyon </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Koreans in Japan Protest Crackdown on Chongnyon </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK3105102894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1006 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3105102894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, May 28 [date as received] (KNS-KCNA) -- 
Koreans in Japan strongly protested against the Japanese 
authorities' crackdown on the General Association of Korean 
Residents in Japan (Chongnyon). 
  Officials under the Osaka prefectural headquarters of 
Chongnyon, some 200 Koreans in Japan and young people under the 
Hiroshima prefectural headquarters of the League of Korean Youth 
in Japan (Chochong) May 25 lodged a protest with the Osaka 
prefectural police headquarters and the Higashi Police Station 
and strongly demanded an apology and return of the confiscated 
materials. 
  All branch officials and compatriots under the Tokyo 
metropolitan headquarters of Chongnyon conducted a street 
propaganda at 19 railway stations in Tokyo over May 26-27 and 
distributed 100,000 copies of a handbill condemning the police 
brutalities. A meeting of activists of the Osaka prefectural 
headquarters of Chochong was held on May 21 to firmly defend 
Chongnyon organizations and more staunchly struggle against the 
Japanese authorities. 
  Protests also were launched vigorously among Koreans under 
Chongnyon in different areas of Japan including Aichi and 
Hiroshima prefectures. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

