Daily Report 
<DATE1>  2 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Friendship Groups Protest Treatment of Chongnyon </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Friendship Groups Protest Treatment of Chongnyon </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0206102394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1002 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0206102394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- Delegates of Japan-Korea 
friendship organisations denounced the Japanese authorities' 
hostile acts against the General Association of Korean Residents 
in Japan (Chongnyon) on May 26. 
  Akira Iwai, chairman of the Japan Committee for Supporting 
the Independent and Peaceful Reunification of Korea, Shigeru 
Tokoi, chairman of the Executive Committee of the Forum on the 
Human Rights of Korean Residents in Japan, Masako Yamashita, 
advisor to the Japan Women's Society and other delegates formed 
a fact-finding team to investigate the suppression of the Osaka 
organisation of Chongnyon and called for an immediate return of 
the documents and materials seized by the Osaka prefectural 
police to the Osaka prefectural headquarters of Chongnyon. 
  They demanded that the Japanese authorities apologize to 
Chongnyon for the suppression and immediately stop search of 
Chongnyon and its affiliated organisations, which is aimed at 
political crackdown. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-27514 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas106_c_94026" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-106 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  31 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Japanese Treatment of Chongnyon Criticized Abroad </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japanese Treatment of Chongnyon Criticized Abroad </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK3105151994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1509 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3105151994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 31 (KCNA) -- Japanese authorities' 
suppression of the General Association of Korean Residents in 
Japan (Chongnyon) has come under fire in different countries. 
The Mozambican Committee for Friendship With the People of the 
Democratic People's Republic of Korea in a statement May 20 said 
the Japanese reactionaries have perpetrated a vicious 
anti-Chongnyon campaign, while scheming to hurl their Armed 
Forces into the Korean peninsula by drawing up a "security 
emergency legislative arrangement", but they are greatly 
mistaken. 
  The Japanese reactionaries must correctly understand the 
socialist Korea, the statement stressed, and added: If they do 
not stop at once their reckless anti-DPRK, anti-Chongnyon 
campaign, they will bump into curses and condemnations from the 
Korean people and the world people. 
  The Nepal-Korea Friendship Association in a statement May 20 
said the police search of the Osaka prefectural headquarters of 
Chongnyon by the Japanese authorities was part of their 
political intrigues to suppress Chongnyon and a crude violation 
of the democratic national rights of the Korean citizens in 
Japan. 
  The Nigeria-DPRK Friendship Association in a statement May 
17 
strongly urged the Japanese authorities to renounce the hostile 
policy towards the DPRK and stop at once the suppression of 
Chongnyon and apologize for it. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

