<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-106 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  2 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chongnyon Supports Leader's Reunification Program </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chongnyon Supports Leader's Reunification Program </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0206102794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1011 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0206102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- Activities to support 
and implement the "10-point Programme of the Great Unity of the 
Whole Nation for the Reunification of the Country" have been 
conducted vigorously within the General Association of Korean 
Residents in Japan (Chongnyon), an authoritative organization of 
overseas citizens of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, 
in the last one year or a little more since the programme was 
laid down by the great leader Generalissimo Kim Il-song on April 
6, 1993. 
  A statement of the Central Standing Committee of Chongnyon 
and 14 press statements by Chongnyon Chairman Han Tok-su and 
personages of various strata supporting the 10-point programme 
were released immediately after the programme was published. 
  Meetings to support and implement the 10-point programme 
have 
been held at 42 prefectural headquarters since the central 
meeting of the Korean residents in Japan. 
  It was stressed in unison at the meetings that the 10-point 
programme of the great unity of the whole nation is a common 
reunification charter of the nation and a great political 
programme which makes it possible to tide over the present 
rigorous difficulties and achieve peace and reunification of the 
country by the united efforts of the whole nation. 
  Rallies, study meetings, lectures and seminars were held 
widely by organizations of Chongnyon and 4,173 cases of mass 
rallies, street demonstrations, motorcade and bicycle parades 
were staged. 
  324,122 Korean residents in Japan participated in the 
signature campaign supporting the 10-point programme in only 
three months. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

