<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 1 (KCNA) -- President Kim Il-song of 
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea Tuesday sent a message 
of condolence to Margot Honecker, the widow of Erich Honecker, 
upon the death of her husband. 
  President Kim Il-song expressed deep condolences to Mrs. 
Honecker and her family and relatives. 
  Recalling that Erich Honecker was invariably faithful to the 
revolutionary cause of the working class for socialism and peace 
against imperialism and fascism and actively supported the 
Korean people in the cause of socialist construction and 
national reunification, President Kim Il-song said the exploits 
he performed in his lifetime would remain for ever. 

