<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   SPA Delegates Meet Cameroon Council Chairman </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SPA Delegates Meet Cameroon Council Chairman </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0106040594 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 0800 GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0106040594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 0800 GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A delegation of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly 
led by Chairman Yang Hyong-sop paid a courtesy visit to chairman 
of Cameroonian National Council on 23 May. The chairman said at 
the meeting that the Korean people, who receive a wise 
leadership of President Kim Il-song, the respected and beloved 
leader, are great people who solve all problems with their own 
might, as well as people who receive great praise and admiration 
from the Cameroonian people. He pointed out that the nuclear 
issue on the Korean peninsula must be solved by dialogue, not by 
pressure or war. 
  The Cameroonian National Council arranged a banquet that 
day. 
Participants in the banquet proposed a toast for the long life 
of great leader Comrade Kim Il-song, for the dear leader Comrade 
Kim Chong-il, and for Cameroonian President Paul Biya. 
  On the same day, the delegation participated in a meeting 
with members of Cameroon-Korea Friendship Lawmaker Association. 
On 25 May, the delegation paid a courtesy visit to vice prime 
minister for Cameroonian territory and administration. On 26 
May, it met with minister of Cameroonian External Relations. 
  While it was in Cameroon, it visited the southwest area and 
the maritime province of the country and toured a crude oil 
refinery plant [wonyu chongje kongjang] and other oil companies 
[chongyu hoesa] there. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
