<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Papers Report on Impressions of Korea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Papers Report on Impressions of Korea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0206102494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1006 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0206102494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["A Country Where Power Is in the Hands of Popular Masses" </F>
-- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA)--Hardial Bainz, national 
leader of the Communist Party of Canada (Marxist-Leninist), in 
his memoirs on the looks of the re-built Korea, which was 
published in a recent issue of the Canadian paper TODAY AND 
TOMORROW, said during his stay in the Democratic People's 
Republic of Korea, he could see at first hand the Korean people 
shaping their own destinies by their devoted efforts, and 
realized that Korea is, indeed, a country where the power is 
entirely in the hands of the popular masses and which was built 
by the people for themselves. 
  The memoir says the United States that provoked an 
aggressive 
war and destroyed everything in Korea in order to block the 
victorious advance of communism after the Second World War, 
blared that Korea would be unable to recover even in 100 years, 
but Korea completed the reconstruction in a short span of time 
and has now set an example of human efforts and creation. 
  The author wrote that through the visit to Korea, he knew 
that Korea has a mysterious strength capable of smashing 
imperialism and that strength is the singlehearted unity of the 
Korean people who are struggling for the national reunification, 
firmly rallied behind the party and the leader. 
  The Nepalese paper DRISTI quoted the former director of the 
Organizational Department of the C.C. [Central Committee], the 
Nepal Communist Party (United Marxism-Leninism), Jeev Raj 
Ashrit, as saying in his impressions of Korea that the entire 
Korean people are feeling satisfied with and proud of the 
socialist life they enjoy and striving to realize the national 
reunification independently and peacefully. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

