<H3> <TI>   Kim Il-song Receives Widow of Anti-Japan `Martyr' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Il-song Receives Widow of Anti-Japan `Martyr' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK3105041594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0405 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3105041594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 31 (KCNA) -- The great leader 
President Kim Il-song Monday received again a visiting Chinese 
woman related to the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle, Hu 
Zhenyi, widow of Chai Shirong, a Chinese anti-Japanese 
revolutionary martyr, and her family members. 
  President Kim Il-song had a cordial conversation with the 
guests looking back with deep emotions on unforgettable days of 
the anti- Japanese armed struggle. 
  He gave gifts to the guests and hosted a luncheon for them. 
  Present were Kang Sok-song, director of the party history 
institute of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of 
Korea, and officials concerned. 

</TEXT>

