<H3> <TI>   `Red Neckerchiefs' Relay to Kim Il-song Begins </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Red Neckerchiefs' Relay to Kim Il-song Begins </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0106052194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0422 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0106052194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 1 (KCNA) -- Relays of members of the 
Korean Children's Union (KCU) carrying red neckerchiefs to the 
great leader Generalissimo Kim Il-song started in cities and 
counties throughout the country on the threshold of the 5th KCU 
Congress slated for early June here. 
  Starting ceremonies took place there. 
  The relay groups were entrusted with red neckerchiefs 
carrying the firm resolve of the KCU members to continue forever 
on the road of the march starting from Mt. Paektu following the 
dear leader Mr. Kim Chong-il like revolutionary forerunners who 
had fought bloody battles for long years for the liberation of 
the country and for the freedom and emancipation of the people, 
flying high the red flag of revolution with President Kim 
Il-song in the van of their ranks. 
  KCU members and people of broad strata warmly sent off the 
relay groups on streets and villages, playing wind instruments, 
waving bunches of flowers and scattering confetti. 

</TEXT>

