<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Daily on WPK Policy on Strengthening Education </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Daily on WPK Policy on Strengthening Education </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0206111394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1018 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0206111394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- NODONG SINMUN today 
carries an article by Yi Yong-tok, vice-chairman of the Central 
Committee of the League of Socialist Working Youth of Korea 
[LSWYK], under the headline "Strengthening Education of Youth 
and Children is Consistent Policy of Our Party." 
  The article says: 
  The lifeline of the revolution is maintained by the new 
generation and the destiny of the country is decided by it. The 
destiny of the party and the revolution largely depends on the 
education of the youth and children, the new generation. 
  From early days the Workers' Party of Korea [WPK] has paid 
deep attention to firmly training the new generation, attaching 
importance to the education of the youth and children. 
  The dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il indicated the road of 
the movement of the Korean youth and children conforming to the 
development of the revolution at the stage where the cause of 
modeling the whole society on the chuche idea is being realized 
and powerfully organizations of the WPK, the LSWYK and the 
childrens' union to follow this road. 
  The question of the education of the youth and children has 
been successfully solved in Korea under the wise guidance of the 
party. 
  The 8 million youths and children are demonstrating their 
stout spirits and noble traits as the dependable successors to 
the revolution and living and striving with the resolution to 
lay down their lives as rifles and bombs in case of emergency. 
This clearly proves the vitality of our party's policy of 
education of the youth and children. 
  To strengthen ideological education among the youth and 
children is an urgent demand of our developing revolution and 
the obtaining [word as received] situation. 
  The imperialists and reactionaries of the world are getting 
more desperate in their maneuvers to isolate and stifle the 
DPRK, the socialist fortress. They are trying to disarm the 
youth and children ideologically in executing their 
anti-socialist strategy. 
  The historical experiences and lessons of the socialist 
movement teach us that the destiny of the socialist cause 
largely depends on the ideological education of the new 
generation. 
  Only when we better educate the young men and women, the 
most 
active and influential unit of the society, and the school 
children, the future of the motherland, can we firmly defend 
Korean-style socialism and successfully carry forward the 
revolutionary cause of chuche to accomplishment. 
  The vice-chairman elaborates on important questions arising 
in the education of the youth and children in the present times 
such as education in revolutionary tradition, class education 
and socialist patriotic education. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

