<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   KCNA Reports Iron, Steel Production Increases </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KCNA Reports Iron, Steel Production Increases </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK3005111594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1021 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3005111594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- Iron and steel 
production is increasing in the Democratic People's Republic of 
Korea. 
  According to data available at the Ministry of Metal 
Industry, the production of pig iron increased 1.8 times, and 
that of steel and rolled steel respectively 1.5 times this month 
till the 25th compared with the same period of last month. 
  In the same period, the Kim Chaek iron and steel complex 
produced over 53,000 more tons of pig iron, 30,000 more tons of 
steel and 23,000 more tons of rolled steel. 
  The production of pig iron has increased by 7 percent, and 
steel by 10 percent at the Hwanghae iron and steel complex. 
  The Chollima steel complex and other steel works also have 
topped their daily production of rolled steel 20 percent as 
against last month. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

