<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Steady Upsurge' in Light-Industry Production </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Steady Upsurge' in Light-Industry Production </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0106101994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1000 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0106101994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 1 (KCNA) -- Officials and workers of 
factories under the State Light Industry Commission of Korea 
have turned out as one in implementing the light industry-first 
policy of the Workers' Party of Korea, effecting a steady 
upsurge in production. 
  More than 30 factories including the Pyongyang Textile 
Combine, the Sinuiju Export Garment Factory, the Hyesan 
Shoe-Making Factory and the Pyongyang Textile Machine Factory 
fulfilled their may plan ahead of schedule. 
  The Anju and Palwon Silk Mills had topped their monthly 
quotas 70 percent in industrial output value and 10 percent in 
production indices by May 27 by introducing valuable technical 
innovation proposals in production. 
  The Tongdaewon Garment Factory, the Kyongamsan Export 
Garment 
Factory and other factories and enterprises under the Unha 
Associated Trading Bureau hit their monthly exports production 
targets more than five days ahead of schedule. 
  Shoe-making factories in Sariwon, Hyesan, Pyongyang and 
other 
areas produced more shoes in May than the previous month. 

</TEXT>

