<H3> <TI>   MITI Minister Hata To Miss OECD Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MITI Minister Hata To Miss OECD Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0206122694 Tokyo KYODO in English 0953 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0206122694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 2 KYODO -- Japanese International Trade 
and Industry Minister Eijiro Hata will skip a Paris ministerial 
conference of the Organization for Economic Cooperation and 
Development (OECD), the trade ministry said Thursday. 
  A tight parliamentary schedule has made Hata's attendance at 
the two-day gathering from next Tuesday impossible, the Ministry 
of International Trade and Industry (MITI) explained. 
Parliamentary Vice MITI Minister Tokunosuke Kaneko and Yoshihiro 
Sakamoto, director general of MITI's International Trade Policy 
Bureau, will fly to Paris instead, MITI said. 
  This year's OECD meeting will address three major topics -- 
growth and employment, reinforcing multilateral trade systems 
and the OECD's role amid rapid international change, a MITI 
official said. 
  Whether the chiefs of the Foreign Ministry and the Economic 
Planning Agency will attend the conference has yet to be 
decided, the official said. 

</TEXT>

