<H3> <TI>   Mieno Says Economic Downturn `About To End' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mieno Says Economic Downturn `About To End' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0106134094 Tokyo KYODO in English 0950 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0106134094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 1 KYODO -- Bank of Japan Governor 
Yasushi Mieno told the Diet on Wednesday [1 June] the domestic 
economy is showing signs of recovery. 
  Mieno told the House of Representatives Budget Committee, "I 
think the downturn is about to end, and the environment for 
economic recovery has almost been completed." 
  He cited progress in inventory adjustments, the effects of 
the government's fiscal and monetary measures and economic 
recovery overseas as favorable factors. 
  Mieno, however, took a cautious view of recovery, saying it 
remains to be seen whether the bright signs will continue 
because of uncertainty over the yen's exchange rates against 
other currencies and employment adjustments. 

</TEXT>

