<H3> <TI>   DPRK Said `Compelled To Withdraw' From NPT </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK Said `Compelled To Withdraw' From NPT </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0206110294 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 1025 GMT 2 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0206110294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yun Ho-chin, counselor of the North Korean embassy 
in Vienna and chief delegate to the International Atomic Energy 
Agency [IAEA], said in an interview with REUTER on 2 June that 
the IAEA is making an unreasonable demand for inspections and, 
as a result, North Korea will definitely be compelled to 
withdraw [taltoerul kangyobatchi annulsu opta] from the Nuclear 
Nonproliferation Treaty [NPT]. Stressing that North Korea's 
intent is revealing its nuclear transparency, Counselor Yun said 
that he is scheduled to have a discussion with IAEA officials 
this afternoon to defuse the nuclear crisis. 

</TEXT>

