<H3> <TI>   DPRK Unable To Withdraw $3.3 Million From BCCI </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK Unable To Withdraw $3.3 Million From BCCI </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2805052894 Seoul CHOSON ILBO in Korean 28 May 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> SK2805052894 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul CHOSON ILBO </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Kim Song-yong from Hong Kong] </F>
  [Text] It was confirmed on 27 May that North Korea has yet 
to withdraw U.S. $3.3 million of the $10 million it deposited in 
the Hong Kong branch of the Arab bank BCCI [Bank of Credit and 
Commerce International] that went bankrupt in 1991. North Korea 
deposited $10 million in the BCCI's Hong Kong branch in the name 
of the Korea Light Industry Commission in 1990. However, it has 
only withdrawn $6.7 million from the bank since the BCCI 
headquarters went bankrupt in July 1991, and is now waiting for 
the bank's settlement to pay $3.3 million, the remainder of its 
deposit. 

</TEXT>

