<H3> <TI>   Reportage, Commentary on President's Russia Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage, Commentary on President's Russia Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Businessmen To Join President </H4>

<F P=102> SK3005022694 Seoul YONHAP in English 0154 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3005022694 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, May 30 (YONHAP) -- President Kim Yong-sam, 
during his tour of Russia and Uzbekistan that starts June 1, 
will be accompanied by six businessmen as guests at 
economy-related events. 
  Chairmen Kim U-chung of the Daewoo Business Group, Cho 
Sok-nae of Hyosung Group, Ku Pyong-hoe of Lucky-Goldstar Group 
and concurrently head of the Korea Foreign Trade Association 
(KFTA), and Chang Chi-hyok of Kohap Group, as well as presidents 
of smaller businesses -- Wang Ho-sang of Dongho International 
and Kim Yun-sik of Shindong Enercom Inc. -- will arrive 
separately in Moscow but travel aboard the president's plane to 
Uzbekistan due to poor air transportation there. 
  It is the first time for businessmen to travel with Kim on 
his chartered plane. 
  "We weren't planning to invite businessmen on this tour, but 
we finally decided to include six businessmen whose companies 
have made inroads in Russia and Uzbekistan to attend only 
economy-related events there at the request of the two 
countries," a Chongwadae (presidential office) official said. 
  Just as some businessmen arrived separately to attend 
economy-related functions during Kim's visits to Japan and 
China, the business representatives will only take part in these 
events, he said. 

</TEXT>

