<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Plans To Apply for OECD Membership </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Plans To Apply for OECD Membership </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK3105053994 Seoul YONHAP in English 0459 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3105053994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, May 31 (YONHAP) -- South Korea has decided to 
apply to join the Organization for Economic Cooperation and 
Development (OECD) this year. 
  The Finance Ministry held the first meeting of a 
working-level committee tasked with preparing for OECD 
membership, headed by Second Assistant Minister Sin Myong-ho, on 
Tuesday morning and decided that the Ministry will study OECD 
regulations in the third quarter and apply to join in December. 
  The 40-member committee will discuss Korea's bid to enter 
the 
OECD with related ministries, analyze its liberalization 
regulations and study the systems of present OECD member 
countries. 
  Earlier, Finance Minister Hong Chae-hyong appointed four 
lawyers as consultants to do research and offer advice on legal 
aspects of the matter. 

</TEXT>

