<H3> <TI>   DLP Secretary-General Returns From China </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DLP Secretary-General Returns From China </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2905081494 Seoul YONHAP in English 0644 GMT 29 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2905081494 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, May 29 (YONHAP) -- The secretary-general of 
the ruling Democratic Liberal Party (DLP) Mun Chong-su returned 
from six-day tour to China Sunday morning. 
  Mun, who was invited by the Chinese Communist Party, met 
with 
senior leaders in China such as Communist Party Secretariat 
member Hu Jintao, vice chairman of the Political Consultative 
Conference Wu Xueqian and Vice Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan and 
discussed North Korea's nuclear problem and ways to expand 
economic cooperation between Korea and China. 
  Mun and head of the International Liaison Department of the 
Chinese Communist Party Li Shuzheng also agreed to exchange 
senior party officials and to cooperate on training of party 
officials and holding seminars. 
  DLP chairman Kim Chong-pil and the Chinese Communist Party 
Secretariat member Hu are expected to visit the other country 
respectively this year. 

</TEXT>

