  [Text] Seoul, May 27 (YONHAP) -- The Korea Development Bank 
will extend a 9.5-million-dollar credit to China to help finance 
a thermo-power project in Jiangsu Province, the bank reported 
Friday. A bank official said the credit will be part of the 470 
million dollars which the World Bank, JP Morgan of the United 
States and two other foreign banks in addition to KDB are 
providing to China. 
