<H3> <TI>   Commodity Fair Opens in Dalian, PRC 30 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Commodity Fair Opens in Dalian, PRC 30 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK3005120594 Seoul YONHAP in English 1139 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3005120594 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 30 (YONHAP) -- '94 South Korean 
commodity fair opened at the Dalian International Exhibition 
Center in Dalian of China's Liaoning Province for a five-day run 
on Monday. 
  About 3,000 pieces of commodities are put on display by 32 
major and medium South Korean firms in the fair sponsored by the 
Korea Trade Promotion Corp. (KOTRA). The participating 
industries include the Daewoo, Sunkyung, Ssangyong and Kolon 
business groups and the Pohang Iron and Steel Co. 
  This is the third South Korean commodity fair to take place 
in Chinese cities. The first Korean fair was held in Beijing in 
1992 and the second fair in Shanghai in 1993. 
  A total of 184 South Korean firms were doing business in 
Dalian as of the end of last year. Their investments totaled 
140 million dollars, about 11 percent of South Korea's total 
investments in China. 

</TEXT>

