<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Plans Technology Promotion Program </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Plans Technology Promotion Program </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK3105001494 Seoul THE KOREA TIMES in English 31 May 94 p 8 </F>
<F P=103> SK3105001494 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul THE KOREA TIMES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The government will carry out a five-year program 
from next year to build up the nation's technology 
infrastructure in a bid to maximize its technological 
competitiveness. 
  The program is aimed at not only developing strategic 
technologies but also enhancing the effectiveness of their 
distribution to cope with the post Uruguay Round era which is 
expected to put major emphasis on technological innovation in 
economic competition in the world. 
  A total of 706.5 billion won will be poured in to the 
project, 417.9 billion won of which will be committed by the 
government and the remaining 286.6 billion won by the private 
industrial sector, the Ministry of Trade, Industry and Energy 
said yesterday. 
  Next year, 40 projects will be undertaken at a cost of 145.8 
billion won, 59.6 billion won of which will be provided by the 
government and 86.2 billion won by the private sector. 
  They include the fostering of technicians to design ASIC 
(application specific integrated circuit) chips and to develop 
technologies for high tech electronic games, the establishment 
of a software industrial technology information center and the 
setting-up of an industrial technology database. 
  Among others are the establishment of a textile industry 
information network, a pilot plant for fine ceramics, and the 
creation of a base for joint research for the development of 
automotive parts. 

</TEXT>

