<H4>    Philippine Senator Speaks </H4>

<F P=102> BK0106092394 Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network in Tagalog 
0500 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0106092394 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Tagalog </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Senator Wigberto Tanada, a human rights advocate, 
has called on the Indonesian Government to stand for the people 
of East Timor. Tanada made the statement during his opening 
speech at the start of the four-day conference on East Timor 
held at the Malcolm Hall of the University of the Philippines. 
The senator stressed his support for the people of East Timor 
who are seeking independence from the Indonesian Government. In 
this regard, Tanada strongly criticized the weak national 
leadership which yields to Indonesia's wishes. 

</TEXT>

