<F P=100> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Visa Agreement Signed With Asian Countries </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Visa Agreement Signed With Asian Countries </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0206020194 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1231 GMT 1 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0206020194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, June 1 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- Recently the 
Deputy Minister of External Relations of Mongolia J. Choinhor 
has visited four countries of the Southeastern Asia including 
Singapore, Indonesia, Philippines and Malaysia and has reached 
an agreement with those countries on mutual visa free exchange 
of citizens. 
  According to the deputy minister, under the agreement it is 
stipulated that Mongolian citizens having foreign passports of 
any kind can stay visiting without visa Singapore and Indonesia 
for a two week period, Philippines three week and Malaysia one 
month. 

</TEXT>

