<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Philippine Handling of Timor Conference Praised </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Philippine Handling of Timor Conference Praised </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0106154394 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 1500 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0106154394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Indonesian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Indonesia appreciates the Philippine Government's 
handling of the Manila conference on East Timor. The conference 
is taking place after the Philippine Supreme Court overruled a 
lower court's ban on the conference. Only Filipinos are 
attending the conference, however, after the Philippine 
Government exerted various effective efforts to bar foreigners 
from attending the conference. 
  According to a press release from the Directorate for 
Foreign 
Information of the Department of Foreign Affairs received by RRI 
[Radio Republik Indonesia] this evening, the Philippine 
Government has also given assurances that the conference is not 
being used as a platform to launch a campaign of lies or an 
international disinformation campaign against Indonesia. In 
this connection, Indonesia respects the sovereignty of other 
countries and the right of their citizens to hold debates. 

</TEXT>

