<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Daily Says U.S. Cannot `Justify' Military Option </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Daily Says U.S. Cannot `Justify' Military Option </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0206052294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0515 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0206052294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["U.S. Military Option Can Never Be Justified" -- KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- NODONG SINMUN today 
lambastes the bellicose outcries of U.S. hardline conservative 
forces driving the situation on the Korean peninsula into 
extremes. 
  U.S. Secretary of Defense William Perry recently took issue 
again with the "nuclear issue" of the DPRK. Talking about a 
"critical situation" which might be created in case "sanctions" 
are taken against the DPRK, he ordered a foreward deployment of 
the extra- large aircraft carrier in a place where it can launch 
into an operation on the Korean peninsula in a few days. 
  Meanwhile, U.S. Senator McCain called for deploying 
additional U.S. forces in South Korea and exercising "military 
strength," arguing that the peaceful nuclear program of the DPRK 
was a "threat" to U.S. security. 
  The daily brands this as a criminal move to commit an 
adventurous military action against the DPRK over the "nuclear 
issue." 
  The news analyst says: 
  A few days ago, the spokesman for the International Atomic 
Energy Agency and the official of the White House in charge of 
national security said they believed the DPRK did not divert 
nuclear fuel to other purposes. 
  Nevertheless, the U.S. hardline conservatives describe the 
DPRK's nuclear program as a "factor of threat to the U.S. 
security." This is a reversed logic of a brigand. 
  It goes without saying that this is an intrigue to justify 
their attempt at isolating and stifling the DPRK, branding it as 
"nuclear criminal." 
  It does not make sense at all that the DPRK which has no 
nuclear weapon and is engaged only in peaceful nuclear 
activities poses a "threat" to the United States far away across 
the ocean. 
  To talk about "threat to the United States" from the DPRK is 
as shameless as a murderer accusing the victim of a crime. 
  The campaign of the U.S. hardline conservative forces is a 
despicable and vulgar act aimed at raising the prestige of the 
U.S. military by deliberately aggravating the situation on the 
Korean peninsula and getting reward for their service for the 
arms trade of U.S. munitions monopolies. 
  With nothing can the United States justify its military 
option. 
  We are not afraid of any "military strength" and will 
sternly 
counter it. 

</TEXT>

