<H3> <TI>   U.S. Stages `Mobile Deployment Exercise' 22-23 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Stages `Mobile Deployment Exercise' 22-23 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2805022794 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1100 GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2805022794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1100 GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to military sources, the U.S. 
imperialists conducted a series of aerial mobile deployment 
exercise on 22 and 23 May, lifting troops from U.S. bases in the 
Pacific area to South Korea. 
  Pursuit-assault planes and VTOL [vertical takeoff and 
landing] assault planes that took off from overseas bases flew 
into the U.S. occupation Air Force bases in South Korea on 23 
May. Prior to this, on 22 May, squadrons of assault planes and 
pursuit-assault planes that left a base in Japan flew into the 
U.S. bases in South Korea. 
  This war exercise was aimed at examining overseas-based 
fighter planes' actual combat ability of rapid mobile deployment 
to South Korea. 
  In the meantime, C-141 and C-130 transport planes carrying 
many troops of the aggression army and war equipment took off 
from U.S. Pacific bases and flew into the U.S. occupation Air 
Force bases in South Korea on 22 May, and the troops and 
murderous equipment carried by air were deployed in areas of 
operations. 
  The U.S. imperialists' planned war exercise commotion is a 
grave challenge to peace and detente of Korea. 

</TEXT>

