<DATE1>  2 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Brunei, Malaysia &amp; Singapore </F>
<F P=101> Malaysia </F>
<H3> <TI>   CNN Urged To Air Mahathir's Arms Supply Denial </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CNN Urged To Air Mahathir's Arms Supply Denial </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0206053994 Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA in English 0430 GMT 2 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0206053994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kuala Lumpur, June 2 (OANA-BERNAMA) -- The Cable 
News Network (CNN) will be asked to clarify its news report 
claiming Malaysia is among three Muslim countries supplying arms 
to Bosnian Muslims in violation of a United Nations ban. We 
want to know their intention for carrying the report, 
Information Minister Mohamed Rahmat told reporters here 
Wednesday. 
  The CNN reported Tuesday, quoting sources, that Malaysia, 
Iran and Turkey had been identified as the countries running 
arms to the Bosnians. 
  Malaysian Prime Minister, Dr. Mahathir Mohamed denied it, 
and 
Turkey did the same. Mohamed urged CNN to carry Dr. Mahathir's 
denial if it wished to be fair to Malaysia. 

</TEXT>

