  [Text] President Suharto considers the current global 
situation as worrisome, even though there are some heartening 
issues such as the end of apartheid in South Africa and progress 
in the Middle East peace process. 
  Speaking at a state banquet hosted in honor of the visiting 
Turkmenistan President Saparmurad Niyazov at Istana Negara 
[state palace] in Jakarta tonight, the head of state expressed 
his concern over the outbreak of conflicts in numerous regions. 
He said the conflicts have resulted in the loss of human lives 
and the suffering of the innocent. This is due to power 
politics, ethnic conflicts, and lawlessness. 

